cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on using deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs) for fine-grained object classification in videos, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the adaptation of different DCNN architectures for this task, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper involves the use of co-occurrence information and fusion techniques, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
